# Slop Scanner — Engineering Rules

Apply to every phase. See implementation-plan.md for full context.

## Code
- TypeScript strict mode. No `any`. No `!` non-null assertions.
- Single responsibility. Max 40 lines per function.
- No magic numbers — use named constants.
- Typed domain errors only.
- Pure functions for detection/scoring logic.
- Explicit async rejection handling.
- Zod-validated env at startup — fail fast.
- Comments explain WHY, not WHAT.
- Max 200 lines per file.

## Naming
- Files: kebab-case (React component files may use PascalCase in apps/web)
- Types: PascalCase | Functions/vars: camelCase | Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE

## Testing
- Co-located `*.test.ts` before shipping modules.
- Mock external I/O only.
- CI must be green before a phase is done.

## Architecture
- `packages/shared-types` has zero runtime dependencies.
- No business logic in route handlers.
- GitHub I/O only through `packages/github-client` (Phase 2+).
